    "comment": "Rationale: Fig. 1A,B: Immuno-electron microscopy of the neuropil of the hippocampal CA1 area and the cerebral cortex localized neurotrypsin in presynaptic terminals, close to presynaptic membranes lining the synaptic cleft. Silver-intensified gold\nparticles reporting neurotrypsin immunoreactivity accumulated at vesicles close to the presynaptic membrane opposite to the postsynaptic density.\nNote, it is unclear what type of presynaptic vesicles contain Neurotrypsin.\nDetection of neurotrypsin in adult C57BL/6 mouse brains was performed as described before (PMID: 12459588) as stated on p. 1863.\n\n26/02/2021 Dnyanada: The paper does not demonstrate the specificity of the anti-neurotrypsin antibody. Literal: Goat antiserum G93 was raised against full-length mouse neurotrypsin.. Experimental description: Two 6-day old mice, deeply anesthetized with a mixture of Dormicum and Hypnorm... (p. 1863)",
